title: Archaeologists unearth lost ancient Egyptian temple 4,500 years after it was built and dedicated to the sun god Ra
description: ARCHAEOLOGISTS have uncovered the remains of an ancient Egyptian temple, dedicated to the sun god Ra. The temple is thought to be 4,500-year-old and is located about nine miles south of Cairo and five miles west of the River Nile. The discovery includes the remnants of a “huge” building covering more than 10,000 square feet....
